<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Jackson Grp Pounds 166,000 in black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JACKSON GROUP, the East Anglian construction and industrial services
company, finished 1992 with a pre-tax profit of Pounds 166,000.
That compared with a deficit of Pounds 1.55m last time and came from
turnover down from Pounds 59.5m to Pounds 57.6m. The outcome, however,
represented a downturn from the profit of Pounds 386,000 reported at the
interim stage, when exceptional income of Pounds 874,000 boosted the
results.
A same-again final dividend of 1p is proposed, making a total for the year
of 1.5p (2p).
