ministers. They admit, however, that he has worked hard with local
authorities to make the council tax a success.
His advisers suggest that he will hope to build a similarly close and
co-operative relationship with the police.
A tough crime policy and a more satisfied police service would leave the
Tory party in the country well-pleased with Mr Howard's appointment.
