FT  28 MAY 93 / The Cabinet Reshuffle: Quotes of the day
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Norman Lamont, former chancellor:
I have always been willing to be judged on my record.
John Smith, Labour leader:
Today's reshuffle is a panic measure by the prime minister, like a
captain of a ship throwing his first mate off the bridge as they head
for the rocks.
Paddy Ashdown, leader of the Liberal Democrats:
This is just a new coat of paint for a discredited government.
John MacGregor, transport secretary:
I think Norman Lamont has had a pretty unfair treatment from the media
really.
