<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Acquisition behind fall at Rolfe &amp; Nolan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Profits at Rolfe &amp; Nolan Computer Services, a futures and options computer
and software specialist, declined from Pounds 1.39m to Pounds 1.22m pre-tax
for the year to end-February.
Last month the group acquired the 80.1 per cent balance of Brokerage Systems
and under current accounting rules had to take that company's losses into
its year-end figures.
Excluding those losses Rolfe's pre-tax profit would have totalled Pounds
1.71m.
Group turnover expanded from Pounds 6.74m to Pounds 11.23m with Brokerage
Systems contributing Pounds 3.27m. Earnings per share emerged at 17.7p
(15.9p) and a final dividend of 4.65p raises the total by 1p to 7.2p.
</TEXT>
